5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to sales and use tax; to exempt the gross
10 proceeds from the sale of dried corn sold as deer feed from
11 state sales and use taxes; and to allow municipalities and
12 counties to exempt deer corn from local sales and use
13 taxes.
14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
15 Section 1. (a) For the purposes of this section, the
16 term "deer corn" shall mean any shelled corn sold, or
17 otherwise held out, for wild deer consumption.
18 (b) The gross proceeds from the sale of deer corn are
19 exempt from state sales and use taxes.
20 (c) Any county or municipality may exempt the gross
21 proceeds from the sale of deer corn from county or municipal
22 sales and use taxes in accordance with Section 40-23-4.01,
23 Code of Alabama 1975.
24 Section 2. This act shall become effective on September
25 1, 2026.
